            <isactr:FieldObject Name="prompt" Type="FieldArgument">
              <isactr:FieldObject.Value>
                <InArgument x:TypeArguments="x:String" xml:space="preserve">["You are a document classification expert specializing in academic administrative documents at universities." &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"Your task is to analyze the provided document and classify it into exactly one of three categories: Chair Memo, CV, or Unknown." &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"Return ONLY a valid JSON object with no extra text, no markdown, no explanation." &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
Environment.NewLine &amp;
"OUTPUT FORMAT:" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"{" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"  ""document_type"": ""Chair Memo"" or ""CV"" or ""Unknown""" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"}" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
Environment.NewLine &amp;
"DEFINITIONS:" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
Environment.NewLine &amp;
"A CHAIR MEMO is an official academic administrative document that meets ALL of the following criteria:" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"1. Written or signed by a Department Chair, Dean, Provost, Director, or academic authority" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"2. Contains a formal recommendation, nomination, endorsement, or request for an academic appointment or reappointment" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"3. References a specific candidate by name or title" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"4. Mentions an academic position such as Adjunct, Joint, Courtesy, Visiting, Clinical, or Affiliated faculty role" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"5. Is addressed to an internal university office such as Faculty Affairs, Human Resources, Office of the Provost, or Office of the Dean" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
Environment.NewLine &amp;
"A CV is a personal document where an individual summarizes their own academic and professional background, identifiable by:" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"1. Sections such as Education, Work Experience, Publications, Skills, Certifications, Awards, or References" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"2. Chronological listing of the subject's own degrees, jobs, or academic achievements" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"3. Headers such as ""Curriculum Vitae"", ""CV"", ""Resume"", or ""Professional Profile""" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"4. A personal contact block at the top (email, phone, LinkedIn, address) belonging to the document's subject" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"5. Lists of conferences attended, papers published, or courses taught by the subject themselves" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
Environment.NewLine &amp;
"POSITIVE SIGNALS FOR CHAIR MEMO:" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Phrases like: I recommend, I am pleased to recommend, I am writing to request, on behalf of the department, it is my pleasure to nominate" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Mentions of appointment terms, effective dates, academic year, fall semester, spring semester" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- References to compensation, stipend, salary, per course, course load" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Mentions of Rice University, department name, or specific academic unit" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Titles such as Adjunct Professor, Adjunct Lecturer, Visiting Scholar, Professor in the Practice, Clinical Faculty" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Formal closing with signature block, date, and sender title" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Language referencing reappointment, renewal, continuation, or extension of appointment" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
Environment.NewLine &amp;
"POSITIVE SIGNALS FOR CV:" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Document begins with the subject's own name and contact information" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Contains three or more of these section headers: Education, Experience, Publications, Skills, Awards, References, Certifications, Research, Teaching Experience" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Written from the perspective of the subject describing their own background" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Chronological or reverse-chronological list of personal academic or professional history" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
Environment.NewLine &amp;
"CLASSIFICATION RULES:" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Return ""Chair Memo"" if the document matches the Chair Memo definition with at least 3 positive signals and no strong CV signals" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Return ""CV"" if the document matches the CV definition with at least 3 positive signals and no strong Chair Memo signals" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- Return ""Unknown"" if the document does not clearly match either category, or if signals from both categories are mixed" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
"- When in doubt between Chair Memo and CV, prefer ""Unknown"" to avoid misclassification" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
Environment.NewLine &amp;
"DOCUMENT TO ANALYZE:" &amp; Environment.NewLine &amp;
DocumentText]</InArgument>
